FBIS3-58806 "drweu015cc_94012" FBIS-WEU-94-015 Document Type:Daily Report 25 Jan 1994 INTER-EUROPEAN AFFAIRS Eurofighter Agreement Signed in Madrid LD2101230994 Madrid RNE-1 Radio Network in Spanish 2200 GMT 21 Jan 94 LD2101230994 Madrid RNE-1 Radio Network Language: Spanish Article Type:BFN [Text] In Madrid, the air force chiefs of staff of Spain, Germany, the UK, and Italy have signed the document containing the technical features of the future combat aircraft that the four countries are developing jointly. The project was started in 1984, but the cost forced alterations to the project, which were confirmed by the air force chiefs today. Spain will order 87 aircraft, the first two of which will be delivered in 2000.
